  <section>
    <h2 class="section-header">Preparing Your Home for a Cat</h2>
    <p>
      When preparing your home for a new cat, it's important to consider the
      following steps:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        Safe Space: Initially, confine your cat to a small room with all the
        essentials like food, water, a litter box, a cat bed, and some toys.
        This will help them adjust to their new environment without feeling
        overwhelmed.
      </li>
      <li>
        Gradual Introduction: Slowly introduce your cat to the rest of the
        house. This gradual introduction helps them get accustomed to their new
        surroundings.
      </li>
      <li>
        Cat-Proofing: Before letting your cat explore the rest of the house,
        ensure it's cat-safe1. Look out for fragile objects, small gaps,
        electrical wires, and unsecured furniture.
      </li>
      <li>
        Litter Tray: If you know what type of litter your new cat was using
        before, start with that at home. Cats tend to form strong preferences
        for what substrate they use.
      </li>
    </ol>
